strategies: No strategies. I went with how I remembered... or didn't.
familiar: The more I recognized some general familiarity of the subject of the image
memorable: the more familiar I rated it.
unique: If there was something about the image I thought was familiar or impressive
realistic: even if I didn't know exactly where or what the image represented
comments: Whether there was something new or unusual about the image.
column26: I asked myself whether this image could be a photo or a photorealistic digital creation. The more I could answer that affirmatively
column27: the more realistic I rated it.
column28: I've done image memory studies before
